******
[2] Cholera - Haiti/Dominican Republic border
Date: Thu 20 Oct 2011
Source: Prensa Latina [edited]
http://www.plenglish.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=408625&Itemid=1


More than 480 people have died of cholera and 1800 others have
suffered from the disease in 2011 on the Haitian-Dominican border,
where a new outbreak of the cholera has been reported, a civil
organization said here on Thu 20 Oct 2011.

The new outbreak of the epidemics affected the bordering region and
cases are increasing, in a zone where there is no drinking water or
centers for the control of the disease. According to the Jeannot Succ
Is Bordering Net, settlers in Bocbanique (a central Haitian
department) have to walk 11.2 miles for medical services.

Less than 2 per cent of the 9 million inhabitants in Haiti have access
to drinking water, while most of the population uses latrines or make
their physiological needs in the open, in places like rivers, or close
to their houses.

